steps:
Since 5 is relatively prime to 17, there exists a multiplicative inverse of 5 modulo 17. We can find this inverse using the Euclidean Algorithm: \begin{align*}
17 &= 3 \cdot 5 + 2 \\
5 &= 2 \cdot 2 + 1 \\
2 &= 2 \cdot 1.
\end{align*}

\begin{align*}
1 &= 5 - 2 \cdot 2 \\
&= 5 - 2(17 - 3 \cdot 5) \\
&= 7 \cdot 5 - 2 \cdot 17.
\end{align*}

